scene.message:
Brown: Hey hey, what's{nl}
with this gloom!{nl}
Let's brighten it up a bit!{waitkey}{ret}

Reiji: The air's foul.{nl}
Smells like the windows{nl}
haven't opened in a month.{waitkey}{ret}

Customer: Heh, fresh faces!{nl}
You don't know a damn{nl}
thing, I bet!{waitkey}{ret}

Customer: Hee hee...{nl}
we're your future selves.{nl}
You'll understand soon!{waitkey}{ret}

Customer: Ahh...{wait_fr:48} folks from{nl}
outside, eh...? Kinda ticks{nl}
me off...{wait_fr:48} Now I've{waitkey}{clearbox}gone and remembered...{wait_fr:48}{nl}
the outside... Gwahh{nl}
...{wait_fr:32} I wanna go outside...{waitkey}{ret}

Master: Everyone, please!{nl}
Come now, let's drink{nl}
in good company.{waitkey}{clearbox}Our fate is the same{nl}
anyway - no sense in{nl}
quarreling, is there?{waitkey}{clearbox}We are all faithful servants{nl}
of Lady Harlem Queen!{waitkey}{ret}

Customer: Back with dumb{nl}
looks on your faces. I get{nl}
it - you met the Queen.{waitkey}{clearbox}A looker like you, if the{nl}
Queen took a liking,{nl}
could've lived in the{waitkey}palace, you know.{waitkey}{ret}

Customer: I get how you{nl}
feel, but you've gotta grow{nl}
up a bit to get by, y'know?{waitkey}{ret}

Maki: ............{nl}
I... I didn't know{nl}
anything at all...{waitkey}{ret}

Maki: You think I'm{nl}
in shock...?{waitkey}{clearbox}But you know, I feel like{nl}
Chisato and I can become{nl}
true friends from here on...{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: So this is what{nl}
that brat meant. We've{nl}
been trapped again, then.{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: A bit surprising,{nl}
but I'd say that was{nl}
Kasai's true nature.{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: Even seeing her{nl}
like that, love stays{nl}
unshaken? Heh, suit yourself.

Mark: Argh, so irritating!{nl}
We gotta take down that{nl}
Kandori bastard fast!{waitkey}{ret}

Elly: {ctl07:1}, do you{nl}
dislike people like the Queen?{waitkey}{clearbox}But pretending to obey on{nl}
the surface, while sticking{nl}
out their tongues behind...{waitkey}the townsfolk are{nl}
just the same.{waitkey}{ret}

Elly: Why doesn't Naito{nl}
come to dislike Kasai?{waitkey}{clearbox}Seeing someone's ugly side,{nl}
isn't it natural to grow{nl}
disillusioned and hate them?

{clearbox}To bare all of yourself{nl}
and still be loved -{nl}
I can scarcely believe it.{waitkey}{clearbox}Could such a person exist{wait_fr:48}{nl}
for me, too...?{waitkey}{ret}

Brown: When you hear{nl}
"Queen," you'd think a{nl}
peerless beauty, right?{waitkey}Eh? Eh? Gets my hopes up!{waitkey}{ret}

Brown: So Kasai was...{wait_fr:32}{nl}
that kind of girl, huh...{wait_fr:32}{nl}
Kinda lets me down...{waitkey}{ret}

{nl}
{nl}
runs deep, doesn't it.{waitkey}

Ayase: Ayase hates it here...{nl}
Feels like Ayase's power{nl}
is being sucked away.{waitkey}{ret}

Reiji: Being true to your{nl}
desires - I don't think{nl}
that's so bad, myself.{waitkey}{ret}

Reiji: A dull ending,{wait_fr:48}{nl}
but maybe that's fine{nl}
once in a while.{waitkey}{ret}

Customer: Hic~ Lady Queen...{nl}
Your paintings are the{nl}
best... so let me outta here.{waitkey}{ret}

Customer: The Queen's art{nl}
is just kids' scribbles!{nl}
Serves her right, I say!{waitkey}{ret}

Customer: A labyrinth of{nl}
sorrow, forgotten in the{nl}
cracks of time...{waitkey}Only liquor can soothe{nl}
my suffering...{waitkey}{clearbox}...{wait_fr:48}Daaaamn it all!{nl}
That little hussy!!{waitkey}Stealing all the good men{nl}
away to her own place...{waitkey}I wanna go to the{nl}
harem toooo!!{waitkey}{ret}

Customer: Even if the stopped{nl}
clock ticks again{wait_fr:32}, my pain{nl}
stays as it was then...{waitkey}{clearbox}...{wait_fr:48}Daaaamn iiit{nl}
that little hussyyy!!{waitkey}{clearbox}Made herself a harem and{nl}
still kept a boyfriend{nl}
on the side!!{waitkey}{ret}Master: No one is allowed{nl}
to leave this market.{waitkey}{clearbox}For the Queen, ruler of{nl}
this market, has decreed{nl}
it so.{waitkey}{clearbox}You'd do well to behave{nl}
so as to win the Queen's{nl}
favor.{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: ...Let's go to the{nl}
palace! We're out of time.{waitkey}{clearbox}No time to play along with{nl}
the Queen's little{nl}
ruler games, right?{waitkey}{ret}

Maki: Inaba's right.{nl}
Let's go see the Queen!{nl}
And get her to let us out?{waitkey}{ret}

Master: If you tell yourself{nl}
you can leave anytime,{waitkey}life here isn't so bad{nl}
after all.{waitkey}{ret}Customer: Wanna meet Lady{nl}
Harlem Queen? She's in the{nl}
Kama Palace underground.{waitkey}{clearbox}The entrance is by the{nl}
casino - but one warning:{nl}
don't make the Queen angry.{waitkey}{ret}

Customer: There's an old,{nl}
grubby mansion further east.{waitkey}They say it leads to{nl}
another world or something.{waitkey}{ret}
